/* =========================================
   Returns Operations Detail Report
   ========================================= */

-- Business purpose:
-- This report joins returns back to the original sale, customer, product,
-- category, and return date. It gives the operations team a clear
-- case-level view of returns and supports the future returns analysis layer.
-- The output is intentionally kept compact so it is easier to explain.

SELECT
    fr.return_id,
    (
        SELECT d.full_date
        FROM dim_date AS d
        WHERE d.date_id = fr.date_id
    ) AS return_date,
    so.order_id,
    (
        SELECT c.customer_code
        FROM dim_customers AS c
        WHERE c.customer_id = so.customer_id
    ) AS customer_code,
    p.product_name,
    (
        SELECT cat.category_name
        FROM dim_categories AS cat
        WHERE cat.category_id = p.category_id
    ) AS category_name,
    fr.return_quantity,
    CAST(fr.credit_amount AS DECIMAL(18,2)) AS credit_amount,
    fr.return_reason
FROM fact_returns AS fr
INNER JOIN fact_order_line_items AS li
    ON fr.line_item_id = li.line_item_id
INNER JOIN fact_sales_orders AS so
    ON li.order_id = so.order_id
INNER JOIN dim_products AS p
    ON li.product_id = p.product_id
ORDER BY
    return_date DESC,
    fr.credit_amount DESC,
    so.order_id,
    li.line_item_id;

Review:

The query provides a clear and useful operational view of returns by linking them to sales orders, customers, products, and categories. The overall structure is correct, and the joins between fact tables are appropriate, ensuring accurate traceability from return to original sale. The selected columns support the business purpose well, and the ordering improves readability for reporting.
However, the use of multiple scalar subqueries in the SELECT clause (for date, customer, and category) may impact performance and should be replaced with proper JOINs for efficiency and scalability. Additionally, consistent use of JOINs would improve readability and maintainability.
Overall, the query meets its reporting objective, with improvements recommended for performance optimization and best practices.
